Job description
🚀 Software Developer – Full Stack (GPS Systems Focus)

Company: I.O Technologies Limited

Location: Kitwe, Zambia

Employment Type: Contract
🧩 About the Role

I.O Technologies Limited is seeking a highly skilled and innovative Software Developer to lead and support the development of a GPS vehicle tracking and fleet management platform.

The ideal candidate must have strong full-stack development experience and the technical capability to design, build, and maintain a scalable, secure, and real-time tracking system.

This role is ideal for a developer who understands system architecture, telematics integration, and database-intensive applications.
💻 Key Responsibilities
• Design and develop a GPS vehicle tracking and fleet management platform
• Build and maintain backend systems for real-time tracking data processing
• Integrate GPS devices via APIs, TCP/IP, or protocol-based communication
• Develop dashboards, reporting tools, and live tracking interfaces
• Design and optimize SQL and NoSQL databases
• Ensure system performance, scalability, and data security
• Maintain and improve existing web-based applications
🛠 Required Skills & Experience

Applicants must have strong knowledge and practical experience in:
• Backend development and system architecture
• Python
• JavaScript
• PHP
• CSS and modern web development
• Database design and management
• SQL databases (MySQL, PostgreSQL, etc.)
• MongoDB or other NoSQL databases
• API development and integration
• Real-time data handling and server-side logic

Strong Advantage:
• Experience developing GPS tracking or fleet management platforms
• Knowledge of telematics protocols
• Socket programming / device data parsing
• Cloud hosting and server deployment
• Version control (Git)
🎓 Qualifications
• Diploma or Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or related field
• Proven experience developing complex web platforms (portfolio or GitHub required)
🌟 What We Offer
• Competitive salary (based on experience)
• Opportunity to work on a high-impact GPS tracking platform
• Career growth within a fast-growing technology company
• Performance-based contract extension
